# 5. いつでもなんて

Saki: Let's make it an awesome session!
Honami: Saki, do you still have a fever? You're a bit flushed today too.
Shiho: Huh? You have a fever, Saki? Why didn't you stay home?
Saki: No, no. I'm fine! It must be from the excitement of thinking about going to the observatory with you guys tomorrow!
Shiho: Are you sure that's all it is?
Saki: Yeah! So let's get started! Come on!
Shiho: Sigh... Okay, but tell us if you start feeling unwell.
Shiho: Let's not have it end like that time...
Ichika: Exactly. We can always practice some other time.
Saki: Cut it out, you don't need to worry so much! I'm glowing with health, see?
Shiho: If you say so. But don't overwork yourself.
Shiho: Okay, let's get started.
Honami: Or maybe we should each practice on our own today? Then everybody can go at their own pace.
Shiho: Yeah, I guess we could do that. In that case—
Saki: Oh please! You don't have to make any accommodations for me! Let's stick with the original plan!
Ichika: But, Saki...
Saki: We already did a solo practice. Now I want to play together with you!
Honami: Well, if you're okay with this...
Saki: AB-SO-LUTE-LY! Let's get started already!
Shiho: Okay. Let's do this...
Ichika: That went really well.
Shiho: Yes, it was really smooth. We kept in sync throughout.
Shiho: You've gotten really good at this, Saki.
Honami: You must have practiced a lot on your own.
Saki: ...
Honami: Saki, are you okay?
Saki: ... Huh? Oh, yeah!
Saki: I was so happy about playing so well that...
Honami: ...
Honami: Excuse me, Saki, but I need to see your forehead.
Saki: Wait. Hona...!
Honami: ...! Saki, you're burning up!
Shiho: Huh?
Saki: I-It's nothing! It's normal for me to be a little warmer than most people...
Shiho: Let me see...
Saki: H-Hey, oww...! Don't squeeze my arm so hard, Hona!
Shiho: You really are burning up.
Shiho: It's like that time when you fainted...
Ichika: Shiho...
Shiho: Why, Saki? Why didn't you say anything?!
Shiho: How many times did I tell you to take it easy? Why do you always do this?!
Saki: Why?
Saki: It's because... I really want to go to the observatory with you.
Shiho: We can go whenever! Your health is more important...
Saki: No, we can't!
Shiho: What?
Saki: We can't go whenever! I've missed out on so much of my life already!
Ichika: Oh...
Saki: Well, see you...
Ichika: Saki...
Saki: Ugh...
Honami: Saki, are you okay? Ichika, can you bring that chair over there?
Ichika: Y-Yeah.
Honami: Sit down, Saki. I'll get you something cold to drink.
Saki: Okay... Thanks...
Honami: I'm thinking of walking Saki home once she feels a little better, if that's okay with you?
Ichika: Yeah, let's do that.
Shiho: ...
Honami: Phew...
Honami: You should be okay now.
Honami: I'm sorry for barging into your house and bossing you around...
Saki: No need to apologize. There's no one else in, and you helped me a lot. Thanks, Hona.
Ichika: You're quick to take charge and always know what to do in situations like this. It's pretty amazing.
Honami: I have a younger brother, so I'm used to it.
Shiho: ...
Saki: Shiho...
Saki: I'm sorry for causing you trouble again.
Shiho: ...
Shiho: Don't say that...!
Shiho: It's not that, but... Anyways, you rest up. Okay?
Shiho: We'll talk when you feel better.
Saki: Shiho...
